1
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:11,240
My name is Tiana.

2
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:12,520
I'm a princess.

3
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:15,120
If she didn’t fall out of Disney,
she must’ve escaped from a mental hospital.

4
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:15,880
C'mon, Tiana.

5
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:18,400
Welcome to Thailand.

6
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:21,480
It's Crazy Kicking Horse!

7
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:24,640
Plant a bomb?

8
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:25,720
Isn’t that a bit too extreme?

9
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:28,040
This will be the last job.

10
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:28,960
Here, take a look.

11
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:30,280
Madam Porn gave the order.

12
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:32,280
I can’t trust Kreetha anymore.

13
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:34,480
How did this thing get to work?

14
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,560
Hi, Kreetha.

15
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,240
Shit.

16
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:37,440
Holy fuck.

17
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:39,440
Why the hell is everyone on this flight today?

18
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,720
Kreetha.

19
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,480
Why don't you set the key first, Madam?

20
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:53,360
Kreetha. Are you seriously telling me…?

21
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:55,960
You’ve got a head just to keep your ears apart?

22
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:58,440
Have you never stored anything in your cerebrum?

23
00:01:58,440 --> 00:02:01,640
Didn’t I tell you to wreck Glamorous Airline?

24
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:05,640
But you made them fabulous!

25
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:06,880
My team...wait...

26
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:07,440
Set the key.

27
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:09,320
Set the key first. Oh right, set the key first.

28
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,960
We really did our best.

29
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,720
Who would’ve known it’d turn out like this, Madam?

30
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:17,840
Maybe it’s just Glamorous Airline’s lucky day.

31
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:21,840
Alright. If you didn’t mean it, fine.

32
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:24,960
I’ll just assume you’re stupid.

33
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:28,160
Wow, you’re savage today.
What, did you eat a hornet’s nest?

34
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,840
The hornet’s nest on your head, maybe.

35
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:30,520
Ouch.

36
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:35,040
Alright, I’ve got a new plan for you.

37
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:39,800
But I’m warning you, this one’s extremely dangerous.

38
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:41,520
But Madam...

39
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,040
No buts.

40
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:44,040
That’s an order.

41
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:47,320
Fix your face.

42
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,640
Fix your face now!

43
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,520
This is the first time.

44
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,120
In a brand-new world.

45
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:38,120
Everywhere I look, it’s so dazzling.

46
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:41,120
People seem so kind.

47
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:45,120
Even that bench over there looks unusual.

48
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:49,680
Oh, is that uncle heading straight for me?

49
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:52,960
Hello. Welcome.
Where are you from?

50
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,520
Where are you headed, miss?

51
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,920
I’m a taxi driver.
Want me to take you?

52
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:01,880
People here are so kind.
I’ve never experienced this before.

53
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:08,640
Tierry, do you see what I see?

54
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,800
That uncle is so nice, right?

55
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:16,680
Miss, are you talking to me?

56
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:19,600
Oh, no. Let’s go.

57
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,520
Come, come. I’ll carry your bag.

58
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:22,520
Thank you.

59
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,520
I’ll take her myself, uncle.

60
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,600
Hey! What are you butting in for?
She’s my customer!

61
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:34,760
I know you, uncle.
Last Friday, you cheated me.

62
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:37,840
What is this, a ghost taxi?
Show me your taxi license.

63
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:44,400
Damn, I was just about to get a customer,
why are you meddling?

64
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,720
Hey, why did you chase away that kind uncle?

65
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,720
He was going to take me.

66
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:57,680
Oh, so you’re a taxi driver too, aren’t you?

67
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:01,200
I’m not a taxi driver.

68
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,520
I’m just here to help you.

69
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:05,240
That “kind” uncle was going to cheat you.

70
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:09,240
Cheat me?
He even said he’d give me a special flat rate.

71
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:12,560
Wow, you really see the world through rose-colored glasses.

72
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,680
So, where are you going?

73
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:17,320
I don’t know.

74
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,720
Huh?

75
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:22,080
Do you have any place to recommend?

76
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:26,080
Of course. The street food district, amazing eats.

77
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:30,640
Yes! It’s time for our adventure.

78
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:34,600
A vast land. A brand-new world.

79
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:37,600
And you’re our new friend.

80
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:49,400
Uh, hey, are you okay?

81
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,640
I’m a princess.

82
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:54,440
Wow, I thought only Thais said random things like that.

83
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:56,160
You talk nonsense too, you know.

84
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,160
I'm telling the truth.

85
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:03,240
Tierry, he doesn’t believe I’m a princess.

86
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:06,040
Tell him.

87
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:08,040
Tell him, I really am a princess.

88
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,960
So, what’s the plan you want me to do, Madam?

89
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:16,440
If I tell you, you’ll be shocked.

90
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,200
Huh?

91
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,200
Not yet.

92
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:25,600
What I want you to do...is plant a bomb.

93
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:26,800
What?

94
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,480
See? I knew you’d be shocked.

95
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:30,480
Here.

96
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:38,880
Take this.

97
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,560
Wait.

98
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,720
What? Planting a bomb?
Isn’t that a bit too extreme, Madam?

99
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,360
So what if it’s extreme?

100
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:50,240
I don’t care. You’re doing it.

101
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:53,040
I promise you, if this works out,

102
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:55,040
it’ll be the last job.

103
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:00,200
The last job?
But I don’t want to do it anymore, Madam.

104
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,640
This is too much.

105
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:05,480
Have you forgotten, Kreetha,
that your mother owes me money?

106
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:07,600
Go think it over carefully.

107
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,440
Will you do it?

108
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:12,920
Or should I have your mother do it instead?

109
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:17,920
She might even be better at planting bombs than you.

110
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,760
Siri, I’m not playing.

111
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:35,000
You guys wanna fight?'
Your eyes are about to pop out.

112
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,440
So, what’s your name?

113
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:51,800
I’m Tiana. And what about you, glasses?

114
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:55,760
Whoa, “glasses”?
We just met, isn’t that a bit soon?

115
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:58,640
I’m All-New. Nice to meet you.

116
00:07:58,640 --> 00:07:59,480
I have to go now.

117
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:03,320
Anyway, try checking out
that street food district I told you about. Good luck.

118
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,520
Hey, aren’t you coming with me?

119
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:07,400
No, I have to go.

120
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:11,280
Where to? Can I come with you?

121
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:11,960
No.

122
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:12,960
Please?

123
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,280
Let me come with you.
I came here alone.

124
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:18,520
I’m leaving in two days.

125
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:20,640
I can’t be away from my kingdom for too long.

126
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:21,960
My people are waiting for me.

127
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:25,320
Hmm. No.

128
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,560
Then can you be my guide?

129
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,240
No.

130
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,640
I’ll pay you.

131
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,120
Even if you pay me, no.

132
00:08:36,920 --> 00:08:40,680
Then how am I supposed to find the DEJAYOU meteorite fragment?

133
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:45,680
What did you say?

134
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,600
Did you say a meteorite fragment?

135
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:52,760
Yes. The DEJAYOU meteorite fragment that fell in Thailand.

136
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:54,560
That’s why I had to come here.

137
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,040
You like stuff like that too?

138
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,520
Yes. I love astronomy.

139
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:02,280
And I collect meteorite fragments.

140
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,480
Whoa, me too.

141
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,480
How many pieces do you have now?

142
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,160
A lot.

143
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,520
In my castle,

144
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:12,520
I even have a room just for meteorite fragments.

145
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,800
A castle? Can you just call it a house?

146
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,800
A real castle.

147
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,360
A real mental case too.

148
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:27,040
Hey, All-New. You’ve been out for half an hour.
Aren’t you going home yet?

149
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:33,080
Yeah, what are you doing here with the Likay heroine?

150
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:37,160
This is my friend, Tiana.
She’s from abroad.

151
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,160
Happy now?

152
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:40,560
I just wanted to care.

153
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:45,280
Nice to meet you.
I’m Sky.

154
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,360
I’m Chaba.

155
00:09:55,320 --> 00:10:02,640
Nice to meet you, commoners, Sky, Chaba.

156
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:06,440
Please, make yourself comfortable.
I’m not pretentious.

157
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:08,760
Even though you look shabby, lowly...

158
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:10,320
We can still be friends.

159
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:16,080
All-New, is your friend crazy or what?

160
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:18,760
If she didn’t fall out of Disney,
she must’ve escaped from a mental hospital.

161
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:19,680
Hmm.

162
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:21,880
Don’t mind her.
She's a princess.

163
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:24,120
Oh, princess.

164
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,120
She wants to be a princess so badly.

165
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:28,160
Princess, prince, whatever...

166
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,040
So, you’re a princess?

167
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,840
Yes.

168
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:36,680
Princess Tiara.

169
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:37,720
It's Tiana.

170
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:41,360
Tiana, your highness.

171
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:45,360
Is this your first time in Thailand?

172
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:49,480
Yes. I came to visit Thailand for the first time.

173
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:54,640
I’ll take you to eat amazing Thai food.

174
00:10:55,640 --> 00:11:00,360
The best. Wanna go, your highness?

175
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:01,800
Of course.

176
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:04,560
Then let’s be on our way.

177
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:04,920
On our way...

178
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,640
Follow me.

179
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:09,640
Follow us.

180
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:31,200
What is this?
Is this a fridge or a black hole?

181
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,440
What the hell...nothing but rotten stuff.

182
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:39,080
Even the cucumbers have gone bad.

183
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:41,760
Don’t they know how to throw things out?

184
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:45,760
If I threw an egg in here,
it would probably come out as a hen.

185
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:54,360
What are you doing, Chai?

186
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:58,560
I’m clearing out the fridge.
It’s full of spoiled stuff.

187
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:04,520
Are you throwing it all away?

188
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:07,640
Of course. Why?

189
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:12,320
Come on, the milk is only two weeks expired.
It’s fine.

190
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:14,760
Hey, two weeks is a lot!

191
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:17,760
Yeah, only two weeks.
Let’s see what else is here.

192
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:22,000
Whoa, there’s so much.

193
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,000
This could save us many meals, you know.

194
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:29,280
Don’t eat it. Trust me.
I bought plenty of fresh food.

195
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:31,360
Let’s eat something way better.

196
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:34,040
Come on, come, come.

197
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:36,680
Wow, I’m drooling already.

198
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,240
So much delicious food.

199
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:45,160
Hey, fried chicken from Jay Jong-Ang.
Ever tried it?

200
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:46,680
Is it poisonous?

201
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:48,960
The chicken’s not, but I am.

202
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:51,240
Very poisonous.
Want a taste?

203
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,960
On second thought, better not.
Let’s just eat this.

204
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:53,960
Let’s have rice instead.

205
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:58,520
Pad Kra Pao.
You like it?

206
00:12:58,520 --> 00:12:59,440
Yes, I do.

207
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:02,040
Well, I don’t. You take it.
I’ll have this one instead.

208
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:14,160
Thank you so much, Chai.

209
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,160
You’re always so kind to me.

210
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:21,600
Every time I come to the Glamorous Airline office and see you,

211
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,080
I feel at ease.

212
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:27,040
Why are you getting all sentimental now?

213
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:30,960
We’re like brothers.
We should help each other, right?

214
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:31,480
Mm.

215
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:35,480
So, for the next flight, I’ll put you to fly...okay?

216
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:36,520
Mm.

217
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:37,520
With All-New too.

218
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:42,800
Uh...All-New as well?

219
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:45,600
But you said I’d fly with another crew member.

220
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:51,600
Yeah, with All-New. Why?

221
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,200
You two fighting?

222
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:59,120
No, but...maybe you don’t have to put All-New on it.

223
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:05,960
No way. This flight has VIPs onboard.
You know what that means?

224
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:09,720
You two can show your full service skills.

225
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:15,720
Who knows...maybe you’ll get promoted
and qualify for First Class training.

226
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:17,200
For your career growth, brother.

227
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:21,520
Mm...do you really think it’s a good idea?

228
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:27,360
Of course, it is. Trust me.
Do your best. Go with All-New this time.

229
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:31,360
Shine bright so everyone can see.
Good, right?

230
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:34,560
Let’s eat, let’s eat.

231
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,640
What, you don’t want to eat?

232
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:44,640
Uh...fine, I’ll eat.

233
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,240
Let’s eat, bro.

234
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:01,720
Are we really sitting here, Sky?

235
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:06,160
Yeah, this is how it is.
Thai local street food.

236
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:08,520
Everyone just sits on the ground like this.

237
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:15,160
Come on, Tiana.
Welcome to Thailand.

238
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:18,080
Let me introduce you.

239
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:22,080
I will introduce Thai food for you.

240
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:27,040
This is grilled pork neck. Say it.

241
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:29,840
Grilled pork neck.

242
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:30,840
Very good.

243
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:34,360
This is sticky rice with chicken.

244
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,280
Sticky...sticky rice with chicken.

245
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:36,800
Sticky rice with chicken.

246
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:38,280
Sticky rice with chicken.

247
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,320
Very good.

248
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:46,240
And this is a special dish for you.

249
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:50,760
Ladies and gentlemen, please welcome...

250
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:56,040
Papaya Salad from Thailand.
Very spicy and delicious.

251
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:56,320
Wow.

252
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,320
Applause.

253
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,480
A wonderful dish.

254
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:03,080
Yes, it’s really good.
Try it, Tiana.

255
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:05,080
Sky, with that many chilies, who can eat it?

256
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,880
That’s not a lot.

257
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:10,600
Local food needs to be spicy and full of flavor like this.

258
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,280
True.

259
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:12,360
Oh, everyone eats like this.

260
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,360
True.

261
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,480
Try it, dear.

262
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:23,320
This papaya salad has been fermented with pickled fish for years.

263
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:30,640
Rich flavor, truly satisfying.
If you don’t believe me, try it.

264
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:33,640
Hahaha.

265
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,520
Alright, I’ll try it then. Whoa.

266
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:45,280
Wait, our local rule says,

267
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:49,720
if you’re eating with strangers for the first time,
everyone must eat together.

268
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:54,080
Uh...I’m full now.

269
00:16:55,240 --> 00:16:57,480
Okay, I’ll make an exception.

270
00:16:58,480 --> 00:16:59,480
Chaba.

271
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,600
Sky, let’s eat together.

272
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:07,720
Er, er...together, together.

273
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:09,960
Cheers.

274
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:14,800
So delicious.

275
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:26,920
Spicy!

276
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:31,120
See? Delicious.
Now, finish it all.

277
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:34,000
Consider it a welcome to Thailand.

278
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:38,560
Chaba.

279
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,600
Alright, plan two.

280
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:51,560
Hey, Tiana.
Want to try a Thai snack?

281
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:52,760
Sure, I’d love to.

282
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:55,120
Then close your eyes first.

283
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:59,240
I promise you’ll like it.

284
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:00,040
Yes.

285
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
Open your eyes, Tiana.

286
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,200
Ahh! Like a lost puppy!

287
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:16,080
What is this?
So cute.

288
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,160
Can I taste it?

289
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:20,560
Of course.

290
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:35,360
So this is what they mean when they say
Thai food is simple, deep, and incredibly powerful.

291
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,400
Powerful.

292
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:42,120
I want my people to taste this dish.

293
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:49,880
Alright, fine. Even though I have that rule
about not eating food from the tropics,

294
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:52,840
I’ll let you eat this.
Just don’t tell anyone.

295
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:53,840
Hold on.

296
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:56,840
Is it good?

297
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,600
It’s good, isn’t it?

298
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,880
Tiana, are you jet-lagged?

299
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,240
No.

300
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:07,080
And you’re okay, right?

301
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:09,200
It’s not too hot in Thailand?

302
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,320
I’m perfectly fine.

303
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:13,320
Do I look abnormal?

304
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:18,080
That’s enough.
Just one bite.

305
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,200
Do I have to try all of these?

306
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,680
Mm-hmm. All of them.

307
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:30,360
Are you sure you can handle it, Tiana?

308
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:35,520
Give it a try, Tiara.

309
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:36,880
It's Tiana.

310
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:37,920
Right. Tiana.

311
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:42,120
So you’ll know what Amazing Thailand is all about.

312
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:45,720
Tiger Power.

313
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:57,640
Correct.

314
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,000
Crazy Kicking Horse.

315
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:03,720
Crazy Kicking Horse.

316
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:16,240
Old Man Jumping Wall.

317
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:22,960
Correct.

318
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:29,120
Girl Falling Off the Bed.

319
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:31,120
Can I skip that one? It hurts.

320
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:34,480
You don’t have to fall.
Just stay on the chair.

321
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:39,520
So, are you drunk yet?

322
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:41,960
She’s not drunk. I think it’s us.

323
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:45,840
Hey, Sky, wait...

324
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:50,960
Come on, since we’re already here,
why don’t you show her a Thai dance move?

325
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:51,960
Good idea.

326
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,480
Alright, Tiara.

327
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:55,160
Tiana.

328
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:56,160
That's correct.

329
00:20:57,880 --> 00:21:04,200
I want to show you Thai sexy dancing, okay?

330
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:13,440
You see me? Okay, okay. 1, 2, 3…

331
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:19,440
And 1, and 2, 3, 4, and a hand...

332
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:24,080
5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10...

333
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:28,120
Sexy.

334
00:21:32,920 --> 00:21:35,360
So? Surprised?

335
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:37,680
This is a dance from PiXXiE,

336
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:39,400
one of Thailand’s top T-Pop groups.

337
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:40,400
Yes!

338
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:41,480
I don’t think so.

339
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,560
What? We just copied it.

340
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:47,320
How about you?
Wanna dance for us?

341
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:51,200
No, thanks. I’m a princess.

342
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:54,120
Doing something like that wouldn’t be proper.

343
00:21:54,120 --> 00:22:01,720
Princess this, princess that.
Or is it that you just can’t dance?

344
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,600
Sit down.

345
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:09,640
Yes, your highness.

346
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:10,920
Music!

347
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,040
I thought you said you couldn’t dance.

348
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:48,280
She's making us look bad, that princess.

349
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:50,040
Call Tid-Gift.

350
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:51,920
We need the queen.

351
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:58,840
Help me, queen.

352
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:02,040
Get over here!

353
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:06,200
What happened?
I'm asking you what happened.

354
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:07,560
Queen!

355
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:11,200
It's that woman in the blue dress!

356
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:12,000
That’s right, queen.

357
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,120
She’s crazy.
She keeps saying she’s a princess over and over.

358
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:17,280
Yes, yes, bring her down a notch, queen.

359
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:18,600
Let me meet her.

360
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:22,880
All-New, who is this?

361
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:26,640
This is my friend, Tiana.

362
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:30,080
Your friend?
She looks suspicious.

363
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:34,760
She either doesn’t have all her screws,
or she’s a con artist.

364
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:39,600
How can this woman speak so rudely?

365
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:44,080
How was she raised?

366
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:49,400
Wow, who do you think you are?
You think you’re so high up?

367
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:55,240
Higher than you. I’m 165 cms. tall.

368
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,440
I’m 159.

369
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:02,840
And I’m Princess Tiana.

370
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:05,080
Princess?

371
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:09,760
Princess?
Princess from where, your highness?

372
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,760
I’m from the Kingdom of PiXXel.

373
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:16,320
PiXXel?

374
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:23,040
PiXXel...or do you mean the PiXXiE kingdom?

375
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:28,960
But if it’s you, there’s no way you’d be in the kingdom.

376
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,840
Oh? You looking for a fight?

377
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:33,840
Don’t.

378
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:42,080
What?

379
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,360
We will protect the princess of PiXXel.

380
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:50,040
We will protect the princess of PiXXel.

381
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,000
We will protect the princess of PiXXel.

382
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:54,840
Royal guards!

383
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:56,840
We will protect the princess of PiXXel.

384
00:24:57,760 --> 00:24:59,760
We will protect the princess of PiXXel.

385
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:02,880
Even uncle here, Sky!

386
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:05,200
We’ve been drinking with him for years!

387
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,200
When did he join?

388
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,240
Is she really a princess?

389
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,200
I’m sad, All-New.

390
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:25,640
I was too busy having fun,
I completely forgot I had to look for the meteorite fragment.

391
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:28,160
I don’t even know if I’ll find it once I come here again.

392
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,160
I don’t know who will end up having it.

393
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:33,680
Don’t be sad, Tiana.

394
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:41,480
DEJAYOU? Where did you get it?

395
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:46,080
Let’s just say...I went to find it for you.

396
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:49,320
I’m overjoyed. Thank you, All-New.

397
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:02,120
Oh boy, you give me DEJAYOU.

398
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:03,880
Aha, aha.

399
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:05,840
Oh DEJAYOU.

400
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:07,680
Oh baby, I’m missing you again.

401
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:09,680
My DEJAYOU.

402
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:49,720
Shit, how did this thing get to work?

403
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:57,360
I can’t trust Kreetha anymore.

404
00:26:58,720 --> 00:26:59,720
Madam.

405
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:04,160
In half an hour, you'll hear some good news, Siri.

406
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:09,160
Let them know what a woman like me is capable of!

407
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:22,440
What should I do?
Think, Kreetha! Think!

408
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:24,440
Think! Kreetha, think!

409
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,520
Hi, Kreetha!

410
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:25,960
Shit!

411
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:26,960
Holy fuck!

412
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,320
What? You startled me!

413
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:30,520
What happened?

414
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,000
Are you all here?

415
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:35,680
Of course, three of us are here!

416
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,360
It's Jane.

417
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:37,040
I'm Noon.

418
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:43,720
And I'm Bow. My name is Bow,
I came here with Noon and Jane.

419
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:44,720
That's enough!

420
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:47,960
Hey, can anyone hear a beep sound?

421
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:49,280
Right, what's that?

422
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:50,680
What is it?

423
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:56,040
Oh, it's my heart pounding.

424
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:58,200
Because there are three beautiful girls right here.

425
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:00,960
Which one?

426
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:03,440
It's you, Sky.

427
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:07,720
See? I told you I'm prettier than you two.

428
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,400
He said it himself.

429
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,000
Hello, ma'am.

430
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:22,240
If you need any additional service, just let me know.

431
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:26,160
Then can you come sit and chat with me?

432
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:27,160
Hey!

433
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:31,440
Come sit and talk about astronomy with me.
I’m really enjoying it.

434
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,800
I can’t. I’m working.

435
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:45,280
Hey, is that a UFO?

436
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:47,680
Whoa, it really is.

437
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:50,920
This is the first time I’ve seen a real one.

438
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,800
Mm. Same here.

439
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:57,800
It’s nice, isn’t it? Sitting here watching
an unidentified flying object together.

440
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:02,640
Have you ever thought about going up there?

441
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:06,520
Of course. I’ve always wanted to.

442
00:29:06,520 --> 00:29:10,520
Then shall we go together someday?

443
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:23,360
Hey, look over there, extra-terrestrial life forms.

444
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:24,720
They’re waving at us.

445
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:26,480
Bye-bye, aliens.

446
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:30,480
Come visit the Kingdom of PiXXel sometime. Bye-bye.

447
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:42,040
How did you all get here?

448
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:46,040
Well, we're flight attendants.
Should we be under a truck or something?

449
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:48,880
But this flight's crew weren't you guys...

450
00:29:48,880 --> 00:29:50,880
Well, those three...

451
00:29:56,960 --> 00:30:00,960
Last flight was exhausting as hell.

452
00:30:01,320 --> 00:30:04,680
Yeah, we’ve been flying back-to-back for so many flights.

453
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:06,840
It’s nice to finally get some rest.

454
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:11,960
Sky, aren’t you tired?
Where do you get all that energy from?

455
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:23,240
Hello?

456
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:25,760
Huh?

457
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:29,840
Yeah, we’re all here together.

458
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:31,840
Sky, Chaba, they’re all here.

459
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:33,720
What was that, Chai?

460
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,000
Huh?

461
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:40,440
No way, are you serious?

462
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:47,840
Huh? Oh, okay, okay.

463
00:30:47,840 --> 00:30:49,840
Huh. Okay.

464
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:57,520
Tid-Gift, why the hell do you keep saying “huh” so much?

465
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:00,400
Chai’s putting us on a flight.

466
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:01,280
Which flight?

467
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:02,000
Right now.

468
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,000
Huh?

469
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:06,360
Now do you understand why I kept saying “huh”?

470
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:08,640
What flight?

471
00:31:09,640 --> 00:31:13,080
Well, the crew that was supposed to go fly,
they went out to eat pickled shellfish.

472
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,840
And guess what, triple food poisoning.

473
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:18,960
So Chai’s sending us to help Kreetha and All-New.

474
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:22,440
God, why would they eat pickled shellfish right before a flight?

475
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,880
Can’t we skip it?

476
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:26,640
Yeah, I’m not going either.

477
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:27,880
I’m exhausted.

478
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:29,880
Huh? You were just dancing a minute ago.

479
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:34,640
That’s a hobby. It’s not the same as flying.

480
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:40,640
But it’s a VIP flight, quadruple pay.

481
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:49,280
Oh, then let’s go!
What the hell are you waiting for, Tid-Gift?

482
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:57,160
So now you know why we’re here, right?

483
00:31:57,160 --> 00:32:01,160
But what about you, what are you doing
standing back there? Slacking off?

484
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:04,440
Oh, I’m just feeling lazy.

485
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:07,480
At least, you admit it like a man.

486
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:09,480
But I might report you to Chai.

487
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:11,800
Go take care of the VIPs, now.

488
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:14,600
Yes, I’ll, I’ll be right there.

489
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,400
Go ahead first.

490
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:17,560
Hurry up.

491
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:18,560
I’ll follow later.

492
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:21,560
Hurry and follow us.

493
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:28,240
What should I do?

494
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:31,400
Let’s move it somewhere else.
Maybe it'll stop.

495
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:37,240
Hey, Kreetha!
What the hell are you doing?

496
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:40,600
What are you doing?

497
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:43,880
I’m squatting.
Trying to build my leg muscles.

498
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:46,640
What’s in that box behind you?

499
00:32:47,080 --> 00:32:48,200
Nothing. Nothing at all.

500
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,200
If it’s nothing, then let me see.

501
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:50,560
No. You can’t.

502
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:51,080
Get out of the way.

503
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:52,080
No.

504
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:53,560
Fine, look then.

505
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:55,080
Shit, is that a bomb?

506
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:57,440
Madam Porn.
She’s the one who ordered it.

507
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:00,080
Damn it, Mom.

508
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:01,600
I didn’t have a choice.

509
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:06,080
No...Tiana...

510
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:08,080
Get out of the way.
I’ll defuse it myself.

511
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:17,000
Are you sure you can do it?

512
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:19,520
I don’t think it’s that hard.

513
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:21,920
Bombs only have two wires anyway.

514
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,960
Shit, this one’s Rainbow Airline style.

515
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:30,560
Do you think bombs only have two wires?

516
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:33,200
Do you think I'm stupid?

517
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:36,640
Go ahead and think!

518
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:40,560
My head's about to explode, I can't think of anyone.

519
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:43,160
Don't let your head explode yet.
Fix this first.

520
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:44,920
Or else, we'll all die here.

521
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:45,920
Let me think first.

522
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:50,640
Go ahead and think,
you won't be able to figure it out.

523
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:54,320
Red, purple, blue, green, yellow.

524
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:00,600
What day is it today?

525
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:04,440
It’s Wednesday. Why?

526
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:06,520
